Consider the following program:

int main()          int f1()            int f2(int X)       int f3()
{                   {                   {                   {
  f1();               f3();               if (X == 1)           f2(2);
  return(0);          return(1);            return(5);          return f1();
}                   }                   else                }
                                          return(X * f2(X-1));
                                        }

Which one of the following options represents the activation tree corresponding to the main function?

A. main -> f1 -> f3 -> {f2(2) -> f2(1), f1 -> f3 -> {f2(2) -> f2(1)}}
B. The activation tree has main at root, f1 as child, f3 as child of f1, then f2(2) and f1 as children of f3, with f2(1) under f2(2), and f3 under the second f1 with f2(2)->f2(1) under it.
C. main -> {f1 -> f3 -> f2(2) -> f2(1)}
D. main -> f1 -> {f3 -> f2(2) -> f2(1)}

